# Final Tool Selection

| Section | Details |
|----------|---------|
| Final selected tool is | HTML, CSS, JavaScript + Canva |
| Reason for choice | Easy to learn, suitable for children, and realistic for the available time. These tools allow our group to create an interactive and visually engaging cyber-safety game efficiently. |
| Rejected tool | Scratch |
| Reason for rejection | Scratch was rejected because our group has limited coding experience, and learning advanced programming within the available time could delay prototype development. |
| Prototype output | Interactive cyber-safety mini game |
| Evidence to upload | Screenshots of the game design and development process, GitHub repository links, Canva design links, and prototype progress updates. |

## Conclusion
Our group selected HTML, CSS, JavaScript, and Canva because they provide flexibility, creativity, and enough features to build an engaging cyber-safety mini game within the project deadline. Canva supports visual design, while HTML, CSS, and JavaScript help create interactive gameplay for children.
